# Docker does not read .gitignore, so this mirrors the rules that
# backend/*/.gitignore and AGENTS.md ("never commit .env, node_modules/,
# .venv/, *.db, or *.log") already state.
#
# The build context has to be this directory because server.js resolves the
# widget outside its own package. Without this file that context is ~45 MB /
# 4851 files instead of ~23 kB / 40, the host .venv and node_modules end up in
# the images, and the log and SQLite cache the service writes at runtime
# invalidate the build cache on every local run.

# Dependencies — the build reinstalls these from requirements.txt and
# package-lock.json. Copying the host's copies also ships macOS-built artefacts
# into a Linux image and shadows the npm ci output.
**/.venv/
**/node_modules/
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc

# Secrets. README part 1 tells you to `cp .env.example .env` and add your key,
# so an un-ignored .env means a student bakes their own API key into an image
# layer. .env.example itself is fine and stays.
**/.env
**/.infisical.json

# Runtime state — the cache lives on a volume, the log goes to stdout.
**/*.db
**/*.db-wal
**/*.db-shm
**/*.log

.git/
**/.DS_Store
